'''彎角骨螺'''（[[學名|學名]]：''Bolinus cornutus''）是一種掠食性的[[海蝸牛|海蝸牛]]。<ref name="WoRMS"/>它們廣泛分佈在[[非洲|非洲]]西岸，喜歡中等水深的海域。它們的殼很大，有刺及呈棒狀，一般都是呈淡褐色或黃褐色，有筆直及很長的[[水管溝|水管溝]]。

==特徵==
彎角骨螺棲息在中等水深的海域，喜歡碎石或岩質基質。它們是[[肉食性|肉食性]]及掠食性的。<ref name="abbott">{{Cite book|last=Abbott|first=R. Tucker|coauthors=Morris, Percy A.|title=A Field Guide to Shells: Atlantic and Gulf Coasts and the West Indies|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|year=2001|page=207|isbn=9780618164394}}</ref>

彎角骨螺含有豐富的紫色染料，一般稱為[[骨螺紫|骨螺紫]]。這種染料是鰓下腺的黏液，用來防禦及協助掠食的。<ref name="abbott"/><ref name="vercauteren">{{Cite conference|first=Vercauteren|last=Joseph|coauthors=Chèze, Catherine; Triaud, J.|title=Polyphenols 96: 18th International Conference on Polyphenols|page=55|publisher=Editions Quae|date=15–18 July 1996|location=Bordeaux, France|isbn=9782738007964}}</ref>

彎角骨螺的殼很厚大，有刺，呈棒狀，[[體螺層|體螺層]]很闊。殼可以長達20厘米。螺旋部很低，體螺層有6-7個[[螺層|螺層]]，每個螺層有2條長而中空的刺。[[水管溝|水管溝]]筆直及長，其上也有短刺。殼呈淡黃色或黃褐色，在體螺層上有3道深色的螺旋形斑紋。殼孔呈卵狀及白色，唇邊、瓣殼質及[[滑層|滑層]]呈杏黃色。殼的外表面都很粗糙。<ref name="radwin">{{Cite book|last=Radwin|first=George E.|coauthors=D'Attilio, Anthony|title=Murex shells of the world: an illustrated guide to the Muricidae|publisher=Standford University Press|year=1976|page=29|isbn=9780804708975}}</ref><ref name="abbott"/><ref name="ardovini">{{Cite book|last=Ardovini|first=Roberto|coauthors=Cossignani, Tiziano|title=West African seashells: including Azores, Madeira and Canary Islands|url=https://archive.org/details/westafricanseash00tard|publisher= L'informatore piceno|year=2004|page=[https://archive.org/details/westafricanseash00tard/page/n143 142]|isbn=9788886070119}}</ref><ref name="rogers">{{Cite book|last=Rogers|first=Julia Ellen|title=The Shell Book|url=https://archive.org/details/shellbook00roge|publisher=Doubleday, Page & Company|year=1908|location=New York|page=[https://archive.org/details/shellbook00roge/page/32 32]|isbn=9781419152924}}</ref>

==分佈==
彎角骨螺分佈在[[非洲|非洲]]的[[大西洋|大西洋]]海岸。<ref name="radwin"/><ref name="abbott 2">{{Cite book|last=Abbott|first=Robert Tucker|coauthors=Dance, S. Peter|title=Compendium of seashells: a color guide to more than 4,200 of the world's marine shells|publisher=American Malacologists|year=1986|page=138|isbn=9780915826179}}</ref>

